Author: Kuala Lumpur
Title: ðŸ”¥[ANN][ICO] Pool Of Stake - Pool for Proof of stake blockchains.ðŸ”¥
Body: ICO Analysis: Pool Of Stake Published on July 9, 2018 By Joshua Larson Proof: https://hacked.com/ico-analysis-pool-of-stake/  Token The projectsâ€™ goal is to increase the profits for small coin holders by enabling a trusted environment to pool funds together. For this purpose, two tokens are used:     PSK â€“ an ERC-20 based token that gives discounts and rewards withdrawal fees.     KEY â€“ acknowledges the userâ€™s initial investment. PSK is their utility token, its sold during the ICO, and it enables users to get discounts on withdrawal fees. These discounts are nothing to sneeze at, and will add up to tons of savings for anyone staking to a pool. PSK is traded freely in the markets and can be stored in any ERC-20 wallet. KEY tokens cannot be traded. They are simply a way of declaring initial PoS coin ownership. Users can buy their PoS coins such as Qtum, Stratis or Ether in their preferred exchanges. Then they transfer their PoS coins into the Pool of Stake full node and via a Smart Contract, they get back a KEY token. The total amount of PSK tokens on the market will be 70 Million, of which 42.8 will be sold during the ICO.  Distribution is as follows:     9% Taxes/ finances/ Legal     20% Security and tech development     42% Marketing/social media     30% Office and management If the hard cap is not reached during the ICO, the number of tokens (circulating and non-circulating) will be distributed accordingly. The idea is to achieve a fair relationship between the donors, the developers, the advisors and the three founders. As such, the total amount will be divided according to the current percentage.  Team Located in Lugano, Switzerland, Proof of Stake has three founders:     Dario Calderoni (Head of Operations): He has 15 years of experience in logistics managing.     Andrea Balzini (CTO): Network engineer since 2015 for a Sirti S.p.A, Italyâ€™s leading technology company in the design and production of network infrastructures and telecoms system integration. It was founded in 1921.     Davide Luigi Borella (CEO): The current CIO of Maveric. Heâ€™s been a coordinator or consultant for numerous companies over the last 20 years including eight years with HQ Engineering. There are nine additional team members and advisors listed, including:     Barotsz Navara â€“ A branding and marketing specialist. Founder & CEO at navarra.is GmbH/Co-Founder at VAUST Studio GmbH/Co-Founder & CEO at Codete GmbH/     Patrick Lowry (Advisor) Co-Founder of Node â€“ a revolutionary high-tech start-up, which disrupts a market niche of wireless transmission devices for both private and commercial use.     Ciprian Filip (Advisor) â€“ Spent eight years at IBM Former IBM. Currently CEO of Fundshing.com, a VC supporting blockchain company launch and manage ICO campaigns.  Verdict This is the most straightforward value proposition Iâ€™ve come across as a reviewer. The Pool Of Stake team is raising $8 million to develop and scale a giant decentralized PoS pool. In the future, the team will take a 10% fee from every stakersâ€™ rewards, unless that staker possesses PSK tokens, in which case they will receive discounts on said fee. The team and advisors have set a realistic goal, and from what is seen so far and appear to be capable and hard-working enough to get it done. Participating in this ICO is for those who have lots of PoS tokens they wish to stake and earn passive income. The PSK token is strictly for discounts on fees and voting.  Risks     Regulations are always a risk with crypto pooling operations. -2     The PSK token is strictly for discounts on fees and voting. There will most likely be very little price speculation, which eliminates that cushion that keeps most cryptos from falling. -1     The voting system they are working on to decentralize the platform seems like it could get complicated. The crypto community is very impatient. If POS makes a few mistakes in the beginning, it could be a disaster. 1  Growth Potential     They already have an MVP that stakes QTUM. +2     Based on future projections, POS expects to reach the break-even point in Q3 of 2020. They expect to have a community growth of 40% every quarter. +2     They want to be set up by the time CAsper starts. Some of the other blockchains they are interested in are: Boscoin, Tezos, Cardano, Lisk, Universa, and EOS.+2     They put out informative blog articles on a regular basis. +1     They are partnered with Maveric, a company that provides startups with the tools and expertise to launch their token ICOs. +2     Then thereâ€™s this crtiical piece of information: â€œBased on future projections and current calculations, we expect to reach the break-even point (BEP) in 2020-Q3. Of course, this outcome may vary, depending on market fluctuations and other events outside our influence. To the best of our ability we have developed a realistic future projection, which is also in line with the future projections of other Swiss blockchain companies. In the initial phase, tech developments and security will be very important. The budget for tech development will decrease over time. Nonetheless, we are working with a team of the best developers in order to stay flexible for changes in the blockchain ecosystem. Marketing is an important step in our plan, with a community target growth of 40% every quarterâ€ +2  Disposition Passive income in crypto is really cool. Genesis Mining is a PoW cloud mining service for the everyman to purchase BTC hashing power. They have over 2 million users. With PoS being the next PoW, and Pool Of Stake being the front-runner for PoS staking pools, this seems like a no-brainer. And there doesnâ€™t seem to be any red flags with regards to the team or idea. 7/10  Investment Details     Symbol: PSK     Platform: Ethereum     Public Presale: 18 June â€“ 20 July (35% token bonus)     Crowdsale: July 20 -Aug 19th (or until hard cap is reached)     Hardcap: 8,000,000 E (8 m euro)     Total Supply: 70,000,000 PSK (70m)     Amount  for sale: 42,780,142 PSK     Github: https://github.com/poolofstake/PSK     Website: https://www.poolofstake.io/     Whitepaper: https://www.poolofstake.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/PoolofStake-whitepaper_ENG_V10_01.pdf     Telegram: https://telegram.me/poolofstake

Author: POOL_of_STAKE
Title: ðŸ”¥[ANN][ICO] Pool Of Stake - Pool for Proof of stake blockchains.ðŸ”¥
Body: We are happy to announce that the first Coin Community Vote is taking place from 29 June 12:00 until 18 July 18:00 CEST. It is the first instance of internal governance in which the community decides Pool of StakeÂ´s direction. You pick the next PoS project that will become part of Pool of Stake.  Pool of Stake is going to conduct regularly a Coin Community Vote. In the future, the vote is going to take place via our PSK platform that is yet to be constructed. The aim is that Pool of Stake stays community-driven and that users have the chance to voice their preference on which coins they want to be able to stake with Pool of Stake. Taking regularly decisions on the next step, instead of deciding at one single point of time the next 10 steps, gives Pool of Stake the possibility to stay agile to the unexpected changes of the crypto market.  So, how exactly does it work? From 21 June at 12:00 CEST you will find on poolofstake.io a list of possible PoS coins that you can vote for. The list consists of projects that either make sense from the business perspective (e.g. relatively high degree of adoption, use of smart contracts..) or were brought forward to us by the community.  So, you simply transfer from your Ethereum wallet 0,000001 ETH to the wallet of the listed coin. Please keep in mind that a transaction needs min 21 000 gas in order to be proceeded.  Read more at https://medium.com/@poolofstake/first-coin-community-vote-895c4c628cec

Author: davide72
Title: ðŸ”¥[ANN][ICO] Pool Of Stake - Pool for Proof of stake blockchains.ðŸ”¥
Body: Pool of Stake- The Pool for Your Blockchain!  Dear community,  We are Pool of Stake- a decentralized pool for staking your favourite Proof of Stake coins. We are true believers of Proof of Stake and we are convinced that it is the future of blockchain. Since we are addressing you, a holder of PoS coins, we suppose you are aware of the benefits of PoS over PoW. Proof of Work is experiencing fundamental limits and Proof of Stake is solving most of them. Proof of Stake makes a great contribution in terms of security, reduced risk of centralization and energy efficiency. This is also the reason why great projects like PIVX, Stratis, Qtum, and many more, use a Proof of Stake consensus algorithm.  Have you ever experienced problems with staking? Have you ever tried staking several PoS coins at the same time? We have experienced the troubles of going offline for just one second and losing coin age, not getting enough rewards due to a small network weight, and many other issues. We realized that individual staking is quite time consuming, research intense, and not very profitable.  Pool of Stake is your solution! With Pool of Stake we pool together our stakes and create greater forging rewards for the entire community. For this, we have created an innovative two-token system, the IOU and the PSK token. Thanks to the IOU token you always remain the owner of your coin and do not need to trust anybody. How come? Because Pool of Stake runs on smart contracts and is therefore truly decentralized. We make your staking more profitable, more secure and easier! On our platform, the smart i.o. database gives you advice on how to optimize your investments and improve your returns. This does not replace doing your own research but it makes performance assessment so much easier.  Decentralization lies at the heart of our project. The team of Pool of Stake is not governing or directing the community. Instead we want to give small coin holders the possibility to have a voice in the native blockchains where we operate. Therefore, we need to collaborate with the core development teams so that we can adopt our pool to the governance mechanisms of the native blockchains. This way Pool of Stake can truly be community-driven.  Have you been looking for a pooling solution for your favourite PoS coin? If yes, then vote for it on our Coin Community Vote! The first vote will take place from 21 June, 12:00 CEST until 18 July 18:00 CEST. Your vote decides which coin is going to be the next to be part of Pool of Stake. If you do not find your favorite PoS coin on the list- contact us and we will make sure that it gets on the list for the second Coin Community Vote!

Author: POOL_of_STAKE
Title: ðŸ”¥[ANN][ICO] Pool Of Stake - Pool for Proof of stake blockchains.ðŸ”¥
Body: It is argued that one of the main benefits of Proof of Stake (PoS) over Proof of Work (PoW) blockchains is that the ones using PoS reach a higher degree of decentralization. Several studies have put in doubt if blockchain based projects are as decentralized as they presume to be. The centralizing effect of big Bitcoin mining operations is one of the cases that reinforce the idea of a lack of decentralization in cryptocurrencies. Here at Pool of Stake, we believe that one of the main factors that causes this unwanted centralization is the use of PoW algorithms to reach consensus. In the following text, we compare the level of centralization of validators in PoW and PoS blockchains by analyzing their geographical location. The PoW projects we analyze are Bitcoin and Ethereum and for PoS it is Stratis and PIVX. We describe each project briefly, and then mention where the biggest mining actors are concentrated for BTC and ETH, and where the network clients are located for PIVX and STRAT.  Read more at https://www.poolofstake.io/blog/pow-vs-pos-showdown-which-is-more-centralized/

Body: I'm report a reflection gathered in a Telegram group:  The increase in difficulty and hashrate on sha256 (combined BTC + BCH) remains spectacular despite the sharp drop in price, we are at + 3-4% every 14 days which implies a + 150% / + 200% per year. During the last relative minimum on April 8th at $ 6500 the difficulty was about 24% less than today's, which implies that a possible return to $ 6500 means a 24% cut in profitability on the cost of energy and longer ROE time.   Today according to the energy consumption index, sha256 (I asked, they count also bitcoin cash) consumes more than Czech Republic. https://digiconomist.net/bitcoin-energy-consumption  I think that if there is a future in the crypto, this will only be on the POS system.

Body: Hi Dev. I want to understand your idea and I have a question for you.  For example: I have 1 000 POS coins A, there are 1 000 000 A coins in network. If I join as forger, I wil share 1 000 / 1 000 000 = 1 / 1 000 reward. If reward = 1000 A coins, I will have 1 A coin for my work.  If I join Pool Of Stake, there are 100 000 A coins. So Pool Os Stake can earn 100 000 / 1 000 000 = 1 / 10 reward from 1000 A coins = 100 A coins. I have 1 000 A coins in 100 000 A coins of Pool Of Stake, so I will be shared 1 / 100 from reward of Pool Of Stake = 1 / 100 * 100 = 1 A coins.  1 A coin vs 1 A coin, what is different? Where is profit/benefit when I join Pool Of Stake?

Author: POOL_of_STAKE
Title: ðŸ”¥[ANN][ICO] Pool Of Stake - Pool for Proof of stake blockchains.ðŸ”¥
Body: Hi, hi quote here below your questions as posted on Telegram, so that other people may know the answers.  The difference is that probably you are not eligible to be a real node or stake node for Coin A because: - you don't have enough coins A to stake or forging - you can't have a PC that could run 365d/y, 24h/d, 60m/h, 60s/m ... and so on - you are not able to respect the protocol about the staking of that coin A (it could be possible that the protocol for staking or forging coin A request to have a "young node" of not more than 1 day (this is an example). - some blockchains will give reward variable based on your amount forged (I.e. Boscoin), the more you have more you get - based on the amount on forge, you have different frequency of reward; it means that if your amount is little you cannot have daily gain

Author: J_o_k_e_r
Title: ðŸ”¥[ANN][ICO] Pool Of Stake - Pool for Proof of stake blockchains.ðŸ”¥
Body: Overall, the list of PoS algorithms falls into two main categories: chain-based and Byzantine Fault Tolerant (BFT). In chain-based PoS validators are selected pseudo-randomly to create the next block. In BFT the act of suggesting the next block and creating the next block are seperated.

Author: J_o_k_e_r
Title: ðŸ”¥[ANN][ICO] Pool Of Stake - Pool for Proof of stake blockchains.ðŸ”¥
Body: So validators that suggest the next block are selected randomly. Then a multi-round voting mechanism determines which block gets finally added to the chain. Unlike chain-based PoS, BFT consensus does not depend on the length or size of the chain after it. Consensus on a block can come from within that same block.

Author: J_o_k_e_r
Title: ðŸ”¥[ANN][ICO] Pool Of Stake - Pool for Proof of stake blockchains.ðŸ”¥
Body: It is important to keep in mind that with PoS design, choices can vary greatly and that a black-and-white division of consensus algorithms is sometimes not possible because a project may be to a large extent PoS-based but have some elements of BFT (e.g. Casper or Neo).

Author: J_o_k_e_r
Title: ðŸ”¥[ANN][ICO] Pool Of Stake - Pool for Proof of stake blockchains.ðŸ”¥
Body: Pool of Stake (PSK) is the first of its kind decentralized pool for proving a bet, the future blockchain. PSK is a completely decentralized, self-regulating and completely carefree pool thanks to the powerful use of Smart Contracts and globally distributed nodes. This project in amazing. Huge potential.

Author: J_o_k_e_r
Title: ðŸ”¥[ANN][ICO] Pool Of Stake - Pool for Proof of stake blockchains.ðŸ”¥
Body: The key to determining which ICO to invest is the "Why Blockchain?" Check. If the company does not have a clear use case that requires decentralization, it fails. @poolofstake does this even further, having the decentralization of Stake Lock evidence as the primary value.

Author: J_o_k_e_r
Title: ðŸ”¥[ANN][ICO] Pool Of Stake - Pool for Proof of stake blockchains.ðŸ”¥
Body: The main goal of PSK is to create a blacksmith pool that will be protected by ERC20 standards, where the owners of PoS coins will be able to assemble together on the given PoS block chain to increase their rewards for forgery. This reduces the requirements for filing applications for forgery and ensures decentralization. PSK also plans to save research time and increase revenues through the database and Smart io platform. The platform will provide an analytical platform that monitors the performance of various moles of PoS.
